Eminem burst on to the US charts in 1999 with a controversial take on the hip hop subgenre, horrorcore.  His first major label debut album Slim Shady EP contains a provocative fest of violent, twisted lyrics and is claimed to be written from the perspective of his alter ego Slim Shady. While offending an array of individuals and various other artists named in his album lead him to become one of the biggest starts on the planet.  Eminem isn't just about controversy and shock value.  The often misunderstood major talent has given white rappers credibility with his string of Grammy nominations , his critically acclaimed film 8 mile and three multiplatinum studio albums.  Aside from Eminem's musical success, he has continually hit headlines with his turbulent relationship with Kimberley Ann Scott and ongoing legal disputes with his own mother.  With an eighth studio album on its way, Eminem continues to take the world by storm.  We take an intimate look into the colourful life and career of this bad boy rapper including interviews with industry experts and unseen footage and clips from his most popular hits.

snippet.title: Status Update
snippet.description: High school student Kyle Moore (Ross Lynch) is uprooted by his parents' separation and unable to fit into his new hometown. After an altercation with the school bully (Gregg Sulkin), Kyle stumbles upon a magical app that causes his social media updates to come true.

snippet.title: Moto 6: The Movie
snippet.description: The Assignment Inc. is proud to bring you yet another epic chapter in the âMOTO The Movieâ film saga.  âMOTO 6â travels the globe in pursuit of the most talented and elusive riders, those that truly live their lives by the twist of the throttle. Jet down to Australia to Jackson Strongâs freestyle motocross haven, along with the champion of the people and all-around shredder, Josh Cachia; take a jet boat deep into the Canadian backcountry and find Kris Foster in his natural habitat, testing the limits of what can be done with a shovel and a dirt bike; back stateside, join amateur motocross superstars Aaron Plessinger and Luke Renzland at the monstrous private track known simply as âDreamlandâ; then itâs off to Oklahoma, where AMA National juggernauts Trey Canard, Justin Bogle, and Jimmy Albertson shred some perfect Oklahoma red clay. From Carmichaelâs legendary compound, at the disposal of present and future motocross kings Ryan Dungey, Jeremy Martin, and Dakota Alix; to the North Carolina Mountains for an ultimate session with two of GNCCâs greats, Kailub Russell and Josh Strang, âMOTO 6â presents the complete and absolute spectrum of riders who are at the top of their trade. The most talented riders on the planet grace the screen, from motoâs biggest question mark, Josh Hansen, to the UK offroad prodigy Jonny Walker, to privateer motocross legend Jimmy Decotis and his merry band of New England rippers. âMOTO 6â stars riders who push the boundaries of themselves and their sport on a daily basis, making their living by truly living.

snippet.title: Lesbian Vampire Killers
snippet.description: Set in a rural town, two hapless friends encounter a nest of beautiful Sapphic bloodsuckers that are enslaved by an ancient curse.

snippet.title: Borderline
snippet.description: On the U.S.-Mexican border, border cop Jeb Maynard is hunting for a human smuggler responsible for Jeb's partner's murder.

snippet.title: Solstice
snippet.description: While on vacation, a young woman believes that her twin sister who recently committed suicide is trying to contact her.

snippet.title: Wyvern
snippet.description: A prehistoric winged creature is released from its glacial icy tomb and wreaks havoc on a small, helpless, and terrified community in Alaska.

snippet.title: The Prince & Me 2: The Royal Wedding
snippet.description: With just weeks before their royal wedding, Paige and Edvard find their relationship and the Danish monarchy in jeopardy when an old law is brought to light.

snippet.title: Jane Eyre
snippet.description: Charlotte Bronte's classic story, adapted by Kay Mellor. After a wretched childhood, Jane Eyre is welcomed to Thornfield Hall by housekeeper Mrs Fairfax when she takes up the post of governess to young Adele. But she finds herself falling in love with Thornfield's owner, the mysterious Mr Rochester.

snippet.title: Inuyasha the Movie 2: The Castle Beyond the Looking Glass
snippet.description: With their greatest foe seemingly defeated, Inuyasha and his friends return to normal lives. But their short period of peace is once again shattered as a new enemy begins to emerge. Kaguya, the self-proclaimed Princess from the Moon of legend, plots to plunge the world into a perpetual night of the full moon. Inuyasha, Kagome, Miroku, Sango and Shippo must once again unite to face a new threat.

snippet.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
snippet.description: A runaway bride does some soul-searching when she's trapped in a snowed-in cabin with her grandmother and an old flame at Christmas.

snippet.title: Foxtrot Six
snippet.description: A former marine and his friends struggle to save their country from a ruthless party leader.

snippet.title: Falling Up
snippet.description: Henry O'Shea (Joseph Cross of MILK, UNTRACEABLE) is on his way to a nursing degree until his dad's sudden death forces him to take a job as a Manhattan doorman. But warnings from his high-strung boss and laid-back co-worker can't prevent Henry from breaking rule number one: Never fall for the beautiful daughter (Sarah Roemer of DISTURBIA, THE GRUDGE 2) of one of the building's wealthiest tenants. In a world where rich snobs never mix with minimum-wage slobs, can a romance between a regular guy from Flatbush and a 5th-Avenue rich girl even make it past the front door? Also starring Grammy-nominated rapper Snoop Dogg, Rachael Leigh Cook (SHE'S ALL THAT), Joe Pantoliano (THE SOPRANOS, MATRIX), and Mimi Rogers (AUSTIN POWERS).

snippet.title: Little Italy
snippet.description: The director of How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days and Miss Congeniality cooks up a sizzling comedy about two lifelong pals whose romance is threatened by their familiesâ rival pizzerias.

snippet.title: Avenging Angelo
snippet.description: A woman (Golden Globe-winner Madeleine Stowe, âTwelve Monkeysâ) who has just discovered she is the daughter of a murdered mafia chieftain (Academy Award-winner Anthony Quinn, âZorba the Greekâ) seeks revenge with the aid of her father's faithful bodyguard (Academy Award-nominee Sylvester Stallone, âRockyâ).

snippet.title: Nothing Like the Holidays
snippet.description: It's Christmastime and the far-flung members of the Rodriguez family are converging on their parents' home in Chicago, to celebrate the season and their youngest brother's safe return from combat overseas. For Jesse (Freddy Rodriguez of SIX FEET UNDER), coming home has rekindled feelings for an old flame, though she won't forgive him for leaving in the first place. Jesse's older sister Roxanna, a struggling actress, has been chasing her Hollywood dreams for years with little to show for it. And much to the dismay of their mother Anna, eldest brother Mauricio (John Leguizamo of THE HAPPENING, THE TAKE) brings home a high-powered executive wife (Debra Messing of WILL & GRACE, THE STARTER WIFE) who would rather raise capital than a child. But when the Rodriguezes learn that one of their own is facing a true crisis, all resentments are forgotten and familial bonds are re-affirmed.

snippet.title: Golden Job
snippet.description: A group of former mercenaries reunite to plan an epic heist: boosting a truck full of medicine held by a foreign intelligence agency to supply a refugee camp in need. But when they find the truck is actually filled with stolen gold, the band of brothers realize they've been double-crossed by one of their own - and putting the situation right will be all out war.

snippet.title: A Christmas Hero
snippet.description: Jenny has fallen in love with Tom, but his ex-wife demands a reconciliation if he wants to see his daughter.

snippet.title: Fittest On Earth: Next Gen
snippet.description: The story of the 2021 CrossFit Games: an unbeatable champion and new challengers, ready to rise.

snippet.title: Godzilla vs. Gigan
snippet.description: A manga artist becomes suspicious of his employers when a garbled message is discovered on tape. As he forms a team to investigate, Godzilla and Anguirus begin their own plan of action.

snippet.title: Holiday Engagement
snippet.description: Heartbroken Hilary hires a hunk to pretend to be her boyfriend over the holidays. But her eccentric mother and wacky extended family just might bring them together for real!

snippet.title: Fanboys
snippet.description: A group of Star Wars fans travel to Skywalker Ranch to steal a copy of "The Phantom Menace," so that their terminally ill friend can see it before its release in theaters several months down the line. The journey takes them across the country, where they encounter a series of fan-related mishaps wherever they go.

snippet.title: Our Dream Wedding
snippet.description: Commitment-shy Haley tries on her grandma's wedding veil and is transported to her future, where she and her long-term boyfriend Scott are happily married with two beautiful children.

snippet.title: Concrete Canyons
snippet.description: A sheriff searches for his son who is accused of murder and on the run in this thrilling crime drama.

snippet.title: Mafia
snippet.description: In the 1970s, a fierce crime boss (Ving Rhames) wreaks havoc on the streets. Detective Womack (Pam Grier) decides to put an end to this organized crime â even if it means breaking the law.

snippet.title: Abandoned
snippet.description: Brittany Murphy (8 MILE, GIRL INTERRUPTED) â in her final film role â stars as Mary, who brings her new boyfriend (Dean Cain of TV's LOIS & CLARK) to the hospital for minor outpatient surgery. But when she returns later to pick him up, he has mysteriously vanished. The police can't help her. Her friends â who have never met him â don't believe her. Is the hospital administrator involved in a creepy cover-up? Could Mary's increasingly frantic state be connected to her previous psychiatric issues? Is it possible her boyfriend doesn't exist at all?

snippet.title: Madame Bovary
snippet.description: Bored by marriage and small-town life, Emma Bovary pursues her dreams of passion and excitement whatever the cost. Mia Wasikowska, Paul Giamatti and Ezra Miller star in the Flaubert classic.

snippet.title: Let's Kill Wards Wife
snippet.description: Everyone hates Wardâs wife and wants her dead. Especially Ward (Donald Faison). But when murderous fantasies accidentally get real, Ward and his pals have all new problems: Disposing of the body. Getting away with murder. Making their 3pm tee time. LET'S KILL WARD'S WIFE, Scott Foley's (âScandal,â âGreyâs Anatomy,â âThe Unitâ) directorial debut, also stars Foley, Patrick Wilson, Amy Acker, and Nicolette Sheridan in a blackly comic caper about helping a friend out of a bad relationship by any means necessary.

snippet.title: Fly Me to the Moon
snippet.description: Young housefly Nat is looking for adventure and hatches a plan to jet into outer space with his two best friends, I.Q. and Scooter. In their homemade space suits, they take a wild ride aboard Apollo 11 all the way to the moon. As their families watch at home, the three flies become the first insects ever to journey into space... but this is no ordinary thrill ride. After a potentially disastrous mechanical problem, these daredevil flies must save the day. Featuring the voices of Kelly Ripa (Live with Regis & Kelly), Nicollette Sheridan (Desperate Housewives) and Christopher Lloyd (Back to the Future), this animated adventures brings Nat, I.Q. and Scooter's out-of-this-world tale to life!

snippet.title: Terror Of Mechagodzilla
snippet.description: Godzilla comes to the rescue when an alien race rebuilds Mechagodzilla to destroy Earth's cities.

snippet.title: Son Of Godzilla
snippet.description: A reporter stumbles upon weather experiments on a tropical island, discovering giant mantids, a cast away woman, and an infant monster that Godzilla must adopt and learn to raise as one of his own.

snippet.title: Invasion Of Astro-Monster
snippet.description: Aliens from Planet X request the use of Godzilla and Rodan to fight off King Ghidorah, but have a better use for the three monsters.

snippet.title: Moto 7: The Movie
snippet.description: MOTO7: A film that rewrites the moto playbook, with the biggest jumps, the gnarliest tracks, and some of the most remote locations a motorcycle has ever touched. Experience Blake Baggettâs newly-developed El Chupacabra Ranch in Florida, one of the most gargantuan home tracks ever made, where Baggett and Ken Roczen enjoy a daily routine of riding light speed fast laps with an almost lackadaisical ease. Three miles away, Aldon Baker trains factory superstars Ryan Dungey, Marvin Musqin and Jason Anderson on a program fit for Seal Team Six. Then thereâs the Smokey Mountains in Idaho, where the Sipes brothers Ryan and Justin go to feel the sweet serenity of a man, his motorcycle, and countless miles of natural single-track. All of these riders are taking moto to territories it has never seen, be that on the stopwatch or the trail map. Thereâs Colton Haaker, the Endurocross phenom whose bike-control and technical abilities are that of superhuman levels. Then of course, Justin Barcia, the exemplar of style on a motocross bike, the guy who defies logic and rides with an amount of panache and flamboyance that is shunned in professional motocross, yet somehow has climbed to the top of the sport.

snippet.title: Trollhunter
snippet.description: The government says there's nothing to worry about -- it's just a problem with bears making trouble in the mountains and forests of Norway. But local hunters don't believe it -- and neither do a trio of college students who want to find out the truth. Armed with a video camera, they trail a mysterious "poacher," who wants nothing to do with them. However, their persistence lands them straight in the path of the objects of his pursuits: trolls. They soon find themselves documenting every move of this grizzled, unlikely hero -- the trollhunter -- risking their lives to uncover the secrets of creatures only thought to exist in fairy tales.

snippet.title: The Derby Stallion
snippet.description: An alcoholic former horse-trainer perceives in a fifteen-year-old boy a unique gift of horsemanship and makes it possible for the boy to conceive his dream and pursue it.

snippet.title: Battle Creek Brawl
snippet.description: Filmed in the U.S., Battle Creek Brawl is Jackie Chan's first crossover movie into the international arena! Chan stars as Jerry Kwan, a Korean man seeking fame and fortune in Chicago in the 1930s, when his serene life is turned upside-down. The merciless head of a mobster syndicate takes his brother's fiance's hostage and forces Jerry to enter a no-holds-barred combat tournament: The Battle Creek Brawl in Texas. With so much at stake, Jerry enlists the help of his kung fu master to train him for the ultimate fight, only to go head-to-head with a rival mobster boss hell-bent on snatching the Brawl's champion trophy.

snippet.title: Abduction of Angie
snippet.description: Paramedic Miranda faces an emergency of her own when her 8-year-old daughter Angie is kidnapped by Miranda's estranged father.

snippet.title: Red River (1988)
snippet.description: Tom Dunson is a cowman who befriends 13-year-old Matt Garth when he is orphaned by an Indian massacre. Soon afterward, with Matt and longtime partner Horace Groot, Dunson lays claim to a piece of south Texas for his cattle ranch. Years later, Matt returns home from the Civil War to find his guardian hogtied economically and desperate to take his now vast herd to market. Dunson and Matt round up a ragtag bunch of cowboys-including gunfighter Cherry Valance and ex-slave, Jack Bird. After the drive is underway, morale is eroded by exhaustion, heat, rain, flaming tempers, sudden violence, the ever present danger of stampedes and the threat of bandits. Mutiny and desertion are dealt with so savagely by Dunson, that Matt rebels and takes the herd and remaining cowboys to a closer destination. But more trials are in store for the men and the herd, including a vengeful pursuit by Dunson and his new allies...

snippet.title: Battle of the Bulge: Winter War
snippet.description: The Battle of the Bulge. Lt. Robert Cappa and his platoon of 2nd Infantry Division soldiers must defend a vital supply depot from being captured by attacking German soldiers. With enemies all around him and allies who are not what they seem. Lt. Cappa must make combat ready decisions in order to slow down and stop the advancing German onslaught of tanks, infantry and artillery.

snippet.title: Supernova
snippet.description: Set in the early years of the 22nd Century, Supernova chronicles the search and rescue patrol of a deep space medical ship and its six-member crew. When their vessel, the Nightingale 229, answers an emergency distress signal from a comet mining operation in a distant galaxy, but as they move in for a rescue, they discover that this isn't the mission of mercy they were expecting. They pick up a mysterious and menacing man with a strange alien artifact, who draws the ship into the orbit of a huge star that is due to explode into a supernova.

snippet.title: Ernest Goes to School
snippet.description: Jim Varney's recurring dim-bulb character Ernest P. Worrell returns in this film as a school maintenance man seeking to obtain a high school diploma.

snippet.title: The Scarlet And The Black
snippet.description: Vatican efforts, lead by Monsignor Hugh O'Flaherty, to save Allied P.O.W.s and downed Allied airmen as the Nazis invade Rome.

snippet.title: Godzilla, King Of The Monsters!
snippet.description: A 400-foot dinosaur-like beast, awoken from undersea hibernation off the Japanese coast by atomic-bomb testing, attacks Tokyo.

snippet.title: Girl in Progress
snippet.description: Grace (Eva Mendes) is a single mom. She is too busy juggling work, bills, and the very married Dr. Hartford (Matthew Modine), to give her daughter, Ansiedad (Cierra Ramirez) the attention she desperately needs. When Ansiedad's English teacher, Ms. Armstrong (Patricia Arquette), introduces her students to classic coming-of-age stories, Ansiedad is inspired to skip adolescence and jump-start her life without mom. While Grace becomes preoccupied with the increasing affections of her co-worker (Eugenio Derbez), Ansiedad enlists the help of her loyal friend, Tavita (Raini Rodriguez), to plot her shortcut to "adulthood". But as her misguided plan unravels, Ansiedad and Grace must learn that sometimes growing-up means acting your age.

snippet.title: Rob-B-Hood
snippet.description: Thongs and Octopus grow attached to the baby they kidnapped for their landlord, which leads to complications in handing the him over.

snippet.title: Fishing Naked
snippet.description: Two buddies in a mountain town scare tourists out of their favorite fishing holes with Bigfoot hoaxes.

snippet.title: If I Were You
snippet.description: When a woman tries to outwit her husband's sexy young mistress, the unexpected consequences include starring as King Lear in a very amateur production - with the mistress playing The Fool.

snippet.title: The Guilty
snippet.description: To all outward appearances, defense lawyer Callum Crane (Bill Pullman) has the perfect life, with a successful career and a beautiful family. That image is shattered when Crane sexually assaults a secretary after a night of binge drinking. After she threatens to go public, the corrupt lawyer hires a young ex-con to silence her for good and save his reputation. Unable to go through with the murder, the ex-con must find and save the secretary before another criminal tries to carry out the job himself.

snippet.title: The Horse Dancer
snippet.description: One of America's most promising young gymnasts, Samantha Wick, is also one of the hardest girls to get along with. When she is cut from the Olympic team she decides to follow her dreams of horseback riding by joining a girls horse camp. With rumors of the camp having to shut down because of financial troubles, one counselor comes up with an idea. Using Sam's gymnastic prowess, the girls start a horse-dancing team to raise money and save the camp!

snippet.title: Moonshine Highway
snippet.description: Itâs the mid-1950s and small-town moonshine runner Jed Muldoon (Kyle MacLachlan), carrying bootleg in his souped-up car, can outrun any federal agent over dangerous Appalachian Mountain roads.  Meanwhile Muldoon, who earns some hefty cash for his efforts, is becoming seriously involved with Ethel Miller (Maria del Mar), the local sheriffâs estranged wife.

snippet.title: Scorched
snippet.description: Woody Harrelson, Alicia Silverstone and comedy icon John Cleese star in this outrageous indie comedy about small-town bank tellers who unwittingly make plans to rob their bank at the same time.

snippet.title: The Assassin's Code
snippet.description: A rookie detective (Justin Chatwin, "Shameless"), son of a dead disgraced cop, works to solve his first major case while under the watchful eye of a ghost-like assassin (Peter Stormare, "Fargo").

snippet.title: Grizzly Man
snippet.description: In this mesmerizing new film, acclaimed director Werner Herzog explores the life and death of amateur grizzly bear expert and wildlife preservationist Timothy Treadwell, who lived unarmed among grizzlies for 13 summers.

snippet.title: Beyond White Space
snippet.description: When a deep space fishing vessel is robbed by a gang of pirates, the Captain makes a daring decision to go after a rare and nearly extinct species. His obsession propels them further into space as the crew spins toward mutiny and betrayal.

snippet.title: The World Made Straight
snippet.description: In a rural Appalachian community haunted by the legacy of a Civil War massacre, a rebellious young man struggles to escape the violence that would bind him to the past.

snippet.title: Mothra vs. Godzilla
snippet.description: A greedy developer unwittingly hatches a gigantic baby moth upon Tokyo, while Godzilla strikes once again.

snippet.title: Shana - The Wolf's Music
snippet.description: Shana, a gifted Canadian First Nations girl, finds a unique form of musical expression on a spiritual journey, becoming a violinist. A captivating coming-of-age story with sensational beauty and spiritual tenderness.

snippet.title: Airborne
snippet.description: When a storm starts closing in, air traffic controller Malcolm (Mark Hamill, Star Wars) sends one last plane into the sky -- but after takeoff, the passengers aboard discover the pilots have been brutally murdered. Suddenly the plane disappears from radar and, one by one, the people aboard turn into dangerous, bloody psychopaths. With time running out, the survivors must unlock the deadly mystery in their midst -- and find a way to land the plane before their ultimate nightmare is unleashed!

snippet.title: An American Christmas Carol
snippet.description: A retelling of Charles Dickens' beloved A Christmas Carol in which Henry Winkler is a heartless finance company president in Depression era New England.

snippet.title: Terminus
snippet.description: Blinded by the light of a falling meteor, David has a devastating car accident, leading to a profound discovery; an extra-terrestrial organism that may contain the secret of life itself. When David goes missing for two days, Annabelle searches for her father only to discover him wandering the forest, without so much as a scratch. Davidâs mysterious reappearance draws the attention of federal authorities and gives Annabelle reason to doubt his sanity. But David has a new sense of purpose, fueled by nightmarish visions. Driven by what he believes is an otherworldly purpose, David must convince Annabelle to believe him and complete his task before government agents can stop him, and before the world destroys itself.

snippet.title: The War Of The Gargantuas
snippet.description: An experimental lab animal called a gargantua escapes from his captors and is suspected to be the creature that is killing people all over the countryside. But when the gargantua from the lab appears at the same time as the evil gargantua, the two begin to battle across Japan.

snippet.title: The Million Dollar Hotel
snippet.description: Tragi-comic, romantic whodunnit set in a run down hotel which plays host to mentally ill people too poor to afford medical insurance.

snippet.title: 12 Days Of Christmas Eve
snippet.description: Calvin Carter is a hard-charging, high-living guy who runs a hugely successful chain of discount stores. When he awakens in the hospital he is met by a no-nonsense nurse who gives him 12 days to relive Christmas Eve and find the true meaning of the holiday.

snippet.title: The Hive
snippet.description: A mass of flesh-eating army antsâ200 million strongâis making its way through the jungles of Brazil devouring every living thing in its path. Called in to stave off the attack is Horace Lennart, a scientist from Thorax Industries extermination service in Los Angeles, and his girlfriend, entomologist Claire Dubois. But when they discover the bizarre intention and origins of the crawling creatures, they fear for the future of the planet.

snippet.title: The Prisoner
snippet.description: A cop goes undercover to infiltrate a deadly prison where a team of mercenaries is being assembled.

snippet.title: District 13 Ultimatum
snippet.description: An elite cop & reformed vigilante reunite to infiltrate a lawless sector of Paris overrun by crime.  Featuring mind-blowing stunts and insane fights derived from the gravity defying martial art Parkour. MPAA Rating: R

snippet.title: Anaconda
snippet.description: A documentary film crew strays into dangerous territory when it takes on a passenger obsessed with exploring the habitat of the world's largest snake.Â© 1997 Columbia Pictures Industries, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.

snippet.title: Shattered
snippet.description: A desperate father fights to save his daughter in this thriller starring Pierce Brosnan, Gerard Butler and Maria Bello. Neil (Butler) and Abby (Bello) have a seemingly perfect marriageâuntil the day their young daughter is kidnapped by a sadistic criminal mastermind (Brosnan) who makes outrageous demands. With nothing left to lose, Neil must take matters into his own hands to rescue his daughter in a high-stakes game where nothing is as it seems.

snippet.title: Pretty Ugly People
snippet.description: Lucy has always used food to escape life's problems. But when this self-titled "fat friend" lures her group of old college buddies to the Montana wilderness, she reveals a new self - skinny, beautiful and still flawed.

snippet.title: What Just Happened
snippet.description: A movie producer desperately tries to save his two films from falling apart while managing the chaos of two marriages that already have. Based on the acclaimed, best-selling memoir by veteran Hollywood producer Art Linson and directed by Academy Award-winning Barry Levinson. MPAA Rating: R

snippet.title: Triangle
snippet.description: When a group of friends overturns their yacht and is forced to take refuge in a drifting ocean liner, they soon find themselves hunted by an unseen attacker.

snippet.title: Delirious: Official Director's Cut
snippet.description: Tom DiCilloâs long awaited Directorâs Cut of his celebrated award winning indie comedy starring Steve Buscemi and Michael Pitt.

snippet.title: Stay Tuned
snippet.description: A husband and wife are sucked into a hellish TV and have to survive a gauntlet of twisted versions of TV shows they find themselves in.

snippet.title: An Eye for An Eye
snippet.description: A SFPD undercover narcotics cop aims to avenge his partner's death and destroy a drug-smuggling ring operated by the Chinese Triads.

snippet.title: The Great Battle
snippet.description: With epic scale and breathtaking action, THE GREAT BATTLE tells the story of the Siege of Ansi, where Goguryeo forces held their fortress against 500,000 invading Tang soldiers in a battle that raged for eighty-eight days.

snippet.title: High Strung
snippet.description:
Ruby is a dancer from the Midwest on scholarship, living her first day in New York City. Johnnie is a British musician, playing for money in the subway tunnels. Rubyâs world is classical and disciplined; Johnnieâs is improvisational and street smart. When a hip-hop battle gone wrong throws these two artists together, they immediately clash but canât deny it when sparks begin to fly. Their lives quickly get entangled in the pitfalls that come with competing in New York City. With the help of a dynamic dance crew called The SwitchSteps, Ruby and Johnnie must find a way to save Rubyâs scholarship and keep Johnnie from being deported. 
  
In an action-packed extravaganza combining cutting edge hip-hop with contemporary and classical dance, the two must navigate their opposing worlds and prepare for a competition where winning or losing will change their lives forever.

snippet.title: The Prince & Me 4: The Elephant Adventure
snippet.description: King Edvard and Queen Paige must track down a missing elephant and reunite a princess, unhappy with her arranged marriage, with her true love. Starring Kam Heskin and Chris Geere.

snippet.title: The Perks of Being a Wallflower
snippet.description: A funny and touching coming-of-age story, THE PERKS OF BEING A WALLFLOWER is a modern classic that captures the dizzying highs and crushing lows of high school. Freshman Charlie (Logan Lerman) is a perpetual wallflower until he falls under the spell of the beautiful, free-spirited Sam (Emma Watson) and her fearless stepbrother, Patrick (Ezra Miller); together, the trio navigates love, loss, fear, hope - and the quest for the perfect song - in this unforgettable adaptation of Stephen Chbosky's beloved novel.

snippet.title: The Tiger (Subbed)
snippet.description: An ex-sharpshooter for the Kingdom of Korea (CHOI Min-sik, OLDBOY) is hunting the country's last tiger. But Japanese forces and vicious local poachers also seek "The Four-Legged Mountain Lord," and will stop at nothing to claim their prey.

snippet.title: Dauntless: The Battle Of Midway
snippet.description: By June 1942, the Japanese Navy had swept across the Pacific. In an effort to change the course of the war, a United States carrier group is positioned off the coast of Midway, tasked with springing a trap on the enemy. During this pivotal battle, the two-man crew of a U.S. Navy dive bomber are forced to ditch in the sea. Set adrift, the men look towards their comrades for rescue; namely, the ragtag crew of a PBY Catalina, who are sent to search for survivors. Amid the vast openness of the Pacific, with days passing and the chance of rescue fading, the men are forced to face their own mortality

snippet.title: Sword Master
snippet.description: In this beautifully shot wuxia epic, a powerful swordsman is haunted by the destructive impact his deadly talents have on others. Weary of the bloodshed and violence from the martial arts world, he banishes himself to the humble life a vagrant, wandering the fringes of society. But his violent past refuses to let him go quietly. The master swordsman must regain the ability to wield his sword and fight those disrupting the peace he so desperately craves. Director Derek Yee joins forces with producer Tsui Hark to bring this classic story of a master swordsman to life. With a mixture of complex emotions and unconventional characters, Tsui and Yee believe their collaboration has created a Sword Master that will both entertain and intrigue.

snippet.title: Inuyasha the Movie 3: Swords of an Honorable Ruler
snippet.description: Many years ago, the Great Dog Demon wielded the Three Swords of the Fang. Upon his death, he bequeathed a sword to each of his sons, Inuyasha and Sesshomaru, leaving the third sword, the wrath-filled Sounga, locked away forever. Now that the Sounga's power has been awakened, these two battling brothers must put away their sibling rivalry and face off against the force that spells doom for all mankind.

snippet.title: Castle Falls
snippet.description: Three million dollars are hidden in a luxurious condominium know as The Castle. Two vicious rival gangs led by Deacon and Shea (Lundgren), are after the hidden cash, but before they can retrieve it the buildingâs janitor Mike (Adkins) stumbles upon it.

snippet.title: First Born
snippet.description: An anxious young mother (Elisabeth Shue) verges on a nervous breakdown after the stressful birth of her child, her husband's continuing indifference and the arrival of a sinister new babysitter.
